{
  "id": "02-orderby-and-collate",
  "title": "`orderBy` is honored on `id` but ignored on `createdDate` and `updatedDate`",
  "hypothesis": "`orderBy` is honored on `id` (~1–5 of 49 inversions on UUIDs sorted lexically). The same syntax on `createdDate` and `updatedDate` produces ~20+ adjacent-pair inversions across 8 alternative encodings — random. So this is not a syntax issue: dates simply are not orderable through `GET /v3/order`. This matters for incremental sync, which would naturally want `updatedDate` ordering.",
  "summary": "orderBy={\"id\":\"asc\"} produced 0/49 alphabetic inversions on UUIDs (effectively sorted). Same syntax on createdDate: ≥19/49 inversions across 8 encodings. On updatedDate: ≥21/49 inversions across 8 encodings. Neither date field is orderable. collate=true on createdDate: 25 inversions.",
